                    EARTH SCIENCE > ATMOSPHERE > AIR QUALITY > EMISSIONS

                    

                
                Definition:

                
                    With respect to pollution, the discharge of gases or particles from a
source such as a smokestack or exhaust pipe into the atmosphere, perhaps
resulting in environmental pollution. With respect to radiation, the
generation and sending out of radiant energy. 
                
                

                

                
